.DT
tell_creator
$MUDNAME$ Creator Help
tell_creator

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
tell_creator -  This method writes a message to a creator, it's mainly meant for debug messages where sending a message to a specific creator is smarter than sending it to players, who will only get confused.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
varargs void tell_creator(mixed cre,
string fmt,
mixed args ...)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^cre%^RESET%^ - the name or object to send the message to
%^BOLD%^fmt%^RESET%^ - the format string
%^BOLD%^args%^RESET%^ - the arguments to the sprintf
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/secure/simul_efun/debug.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method writes a message to a creator, it's mainly meant
for debug messages where sending a message to a specific
creator is smarter than sending it to players, who will only get confused.
Typically you should use debug_printf() instead of this.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
debug_printf

.EP

